
Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets - J.K. Rowling
Harry returns to Hogwarts for his second year and uncovers dark secrets within the school as students are mysteriously petrified.

Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows - J.K. Rowling
The final battle between Harry and Voldemort unfolds as Harry and his friends search for Horcruxes to destroy the Dark Lord once and for all.

Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire - J.K. Rowling
Harry competes in the dangerous Triwizard Tournament, facing dragons, underwater challenges, and a terrifying graveyard encounter with Voldemort.

Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince - J.K. Rowling
In his sixth year, Harry learns about Voldemort’s past and discovers a mysterious potion book belonging to the Half-Blood Prince.

Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix - J.K. Rowling
Harry faces his toughest year yet, battling the Ministry of Magic’s interference at Hogwarts and training a group of students to resist Voldemort.

Harry Potter and the Philosopher’s Stone - J.K. Rowling
Harry discovers he’s a wizard on his eleventh birthday and enters a world of magic, friends, and the dark mystery of the Philosopher’s Stone.

Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban - J.K. Rowling
Harry learns about Sirius Black, an escaped prisoner who may be linked to his parents’ murder and uncovers secrets about his own family.

I Am Number Four - Pittacus Lore
An alien teenager on Earth with special abilities is hunted by a rival alien species and must discover his powers to survive.

Ikigai - Hector Garcia
This book explores the Japanese concept of 'ikigai,' or life’s purpose, offering insights into how to live a fulfilled, joyful life.

Kaizen - Sarah Harvey
A practical guide to implementing the Japanese technique of Kaizen, focusing on continuous improvement and small steps toward lasting change.

Meditations - Marcus Aurelius
A collection of philosophical reflections by the Roman Emperor, touching on Stoic principles of discipline, integrity, and inner peace.

Soul - Olivia Wilson
A contemporary exploration of self-discovery and personal growth, encouraging readers to find peace and purpose in their lives.

Stay with Me - Claudia Wilson
A poignant love story that explores themes of loyalty, sacrifice, and enduring love through life's hardships and triumphs.

The Art of War - Sun Tzu
A classic treatise on strategy and military tactics, offering timeless insights into conflict, leadership, and effective decision-making.

The Brothers Karamazov - Fyodor Dostoevsky
A philosophical novel that delves into faith, family, and morality as three brothers confront their father’s murder.

The Count of Monte Cristo - Alexandre Dumas
A tale of betrayal and revenge, following Edmond Dantès as he escapes prison and seeks justice against those who wronged him.

The Darkest Minds - Alexandra Bracken
In a dystopian world, children with superhuman abilities are feared and hunted by the government, and one girl seeks freedom.

The Great Gatsby - F. Scott Fitzgerald
A depiction of the American Dream’s decline in the Jazz Age, focusing on Jay Gatsby's obsession with wealth and love.

The True Love Story - Takehiro Kanegi
A heartfelt exploration of relationships, loyalty, and the enduring nature of true love against life’s challenges.

The Young Wizard - Aaron Loeb
A fantasy adventure that follows a young wizard’s journey through magical realms and his quest to master his powers.

War and Peace - Leo Tolstoy
A sweeping epic set during the Napoleonic Wars, examining the lives of Russian aristocrats amidst the tumult of history.